HEADWORD: Malleation
<hw>Mal`le*a"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>malleatio</ets>: cf. OF. <ets>mall⟦eacute⟧ation</ets>.]</ety>
<def>The act or process of beating into a plate, sheet, or leaf, as a
metal; extension by beating.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

